From Paul Yee Subject Re Booting from B drive In article nova Mohammad Razi Khan writes Gordon Lang writes David Weisberger wrote I have a drive as drive How can I make the system boot from my B drive intermediate reply suggesting cable switch deleted I have AMI bios I have poked around the bios but haven't tried this but somewhere it says BOOT A C I would assume that you could probably slip in a b althoug I haven't tried it and don't mess with your CMOS unless you know what your doing I hate to burst your bubble but you cannot slip in a B to that particular AMI BIOS That setting only allows you to set the boot order of the floppy A with respect to the primary HD C check A first then C or check C then A Gordon Lang Mohammad Khan After July ' please send mail to Regards Paul Yee